<br>
What behavior would this be exactly?  Is &quot;behavior&quot; in the context of a picture of A/A' s fornicating out in the desert and beheading people's cats, or is it more in the sense of not blindly accepting other people's ideas as our own?  I wouldn't have much in the way of &quot;behavior&quot; to change.  If God revealed himself to me, then after I got my head checked I would be good to go.  Once God revealed himself to me, I would ask him to iron out all the inconsistencies in the book man wrote about him so I could follow the true path he wants me to be on.  If he tells me that my potty mouth and rock music are much more evil than just forms of expression, then I would give them up.  Other than that, I am a decent person, and my guess is that God would be pretty happy with who I am.  <br>
<br>
As for the context in which I use &quot;fundie&quot; or &quot;bible thumper&quot;, I only apply that to people who either push their unwanted views on others, people who can't think for themselves because everything is &quot;God's plan&quot; or people who are intolerant of other people's beliefs because they are always &quot;right&quot;.  I don't think there is anything wrong with having strong faith.  I think faith can be a beautiful thing if used responsibly.  <br>
<br>
