You betcha!  Depending on which god was proven, the nature and extent of the proof, I would adopt those doctrines and habits that were necessary to meet god’s standards for salvation.  (Eternal heavenly bliss?  Temporary mortal gratification?  Eternal damnation? No contest.)  Mind you, the proof has to be pretty steep, the being has to be worthy and the goal has to hold merit.  No heaven?  No point.  Selfish petty god? Why would I work towards a crappy boss when I can have oblivion?  I am already a decent person, I doubt there would be much to actually change (depending on the god proven.)  Only a stubborn fool would not, once proof is established.<br>
<br>
